  "body": "### Description\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: User still receives notifications from a contact he has removed.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nWhen user removes a contact we may assume that he does not want to receive incoming message notifications from him. \r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nThere is no notification when first message is received from an unknown contact. **But**, when this contact is added and then removed the notifications are still being received.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n- Open Status\r\n- User 1: Start a chat with User 2\r\n- User 2: Accept User 1 as contact\r\n- User 2: Delete User 1 from contacts\r\n- User 2: Put Status in the background\r\n- User 1: Send message to User 2. He sees notification\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: nightly, March 1\r\n* Operating System: iOS 11.2.1. Not tested on Android",
